<item>
            <title>[OAK-6864] IndexUpdate should disable superseded indexes only during an async cycle run</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-6864</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Once an superseding index is indexed (has &lt;tt&gt;:disableIndexesOnNextCycle&lt;/tt&gt; flag) then IndexUpdate disables the superseded index the next time superseding index is indexed. So, if we have and async index running in nrt mode too - then nrt updates also disable indexes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should have a more controlled disabling action (apart from concurrent nrt/sync updates would likely conflict with each to fail the commit) - do it in async cycle.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note: This is only relevant when superseding index is an async index - superseding sync indexes would continue to work as earlier.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
